                  <handDesc>
                    <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                    <seg type="rubrication">
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                    </seg>
                    <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                    <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#128r" facs="128">fols. 128r, </locus> (Ps. 150), <locus target="#137r #137v #138r" facs="137 138">137r, 137v, 138r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                    </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#2r" facs="002">Fol. 2r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with patron postrate before them</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#26v" facs="027">Fol. 26v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref> (center), <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/> (right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#27r" facs="027">Fol. 27r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> (right), <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/> (left)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#38r" facs="038">Fol. 38r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref> , with <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> (left) and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5695John">John</persName> (right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#56v" facs="057">Fol. 56v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> and Birutawit</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#57r" facs="057">Fol. 57r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref> Enthroned, surrounded by the four living creatures and a patron protrate below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#129v" facs="130">Fol. 129v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1062CoronationMary">Coronation of Mary</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#160v" facs="161">Fol. 160v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1101GodFatherOrb"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1101GodFatherOrb</span></ref> (on the right) gives something to a saint (left); an <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/> blows a ram’s horn (lower right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#161v" facs="162">Fol. 161v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref> and the raising of Adam and Eve</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d10">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#45v" facs="046">fols. 45v, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#1r #1v #13r #29r #31r #31v #32r #32v #47v #55r #68r #68v #74v #83r #90v #113v #116r #122v #141r" facs="001 002 013 029 031 032 033 048 055 068 069 075 083 091 114 116 123 141">1r, 1v, 13r, 29r, 31r, 31v, 32r, 32v, 47v, 55r, 68r, 68v, 74v, 83r, 90v, 113v, 116r, 122v, 141r, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                    <locus target="#8v #17r #26r" facs="009 017 026">8v, 17r, 26r, </locus> (full stops connected with alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#37v #89r #148v #162v" facs="038 089 149 163">37v, 89r, 148v, 162v, </locus> (full stops between lines of red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#52v #62r #74r" facs="053 062 075">52v, 62r, 74r</locus> (line of red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#162v" facs="163">Fol. 162v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    List of Feast days for the month of Mäggabit
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#7v #9r #9v #14v #22r" facs="008 009 010 015 022">Fols. 7v, 9r, 9v, 14v, 22r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#34r #69v #79v #89r #91v" facs="034 070 080 089 092">Fols. 34r, 69v, 79v, 89r, 91v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#94r" facs="094">Fol. 94r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    erasure markings are visible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#5r #6r #6v #13v #34v" facs="005 006 007 014 035">Fols. 5r, 6r, 6v, 13v, 34v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#14v #37r #49r #5r #8r #14v" facs="015 037 049 005 008 015">Fols. 14v, 37r, 49r, 5r, 8r, 14v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., 14v, 37r, 49r). Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line. (e.g.,  5r, 8r, 14v)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
